      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T16:28:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, this could certainly get us closer to doing that.\n\nIf Wuffs can do subsetting in a way that prevents allocating memory for the entire image, that would fit with the original goal of subsetting. If SkWuffsCodec does it just by drawing a subset, there\u0027s less of a benefit to doing it here (though I suppose it still saves some memory).",
      "parentUuid": "14c8a4d0_c944520e",
      "revId": "9dc6192c17dff2c5f0aae49b51fc2c6c4050d255",
