      "writtenOn": "2019-02-22T21:38:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Out of curiosity, if the source file had a color profile (GIF can\u0027t, but e.g. PNG can), how would that be represented? Another configurating call on srcInfo here, or by some other mechanism (on the SkBitmap / the SkCanvas / the SkPaint)?",
      "revId": "9dc6192c17dff2c5f0aae49b51fc2c6c4050d255",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b16e64a8_41599fc9",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 443,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T16:28:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, that would be part of getInfo(). When you create the SkEncodedInfo, you can supply an skcms_ICCProfile, which getInfo() will convert to an SkColorSpace.\n\nYou\u0027re right to question this, though - not all skcms_ICCProfile have corresponding SkColorSpaces. In that case, we (currently) convert to SRGB. But the approach in this CL does not handle that case.\n\nI talked about this with brianosman@. skcms_ICCProfiles that do *not* have corresponding SkColorSpaces are very rare. It *might* make sense for them to have a special case that requires an extra temporary memory allocation. OTOH, maybe we should stick with the old approach and use the same code for all images.",
      "parentUuid": "015b1133_b99783e6",
      "revId": "9dc6192c17dff2c5f0aae49b51fc2c6c4050d255",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "61e65f80_ca472483",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 444,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-22T21:38:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just confirming that you want Unpremul. Wuffs can generate Premul, if it would be faster in the subsequent drawBitmap call.\n\nSpecifically for GIF (which has only 0% or 100% transparency), the src pixels are actually in both Premul and Unpremul form (so conversion is a no-op), but some day in the future, we might use re-use this code for other image formats.\n\nIn any case, I\u0027m talking about performance, not just correctness. Perhaps we should punt this to a future CL (with its own benchmark measurements)...",
      "revId": "9dc6192c17dff2c5f0aae49b51fc2c6c4050d255",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "751469a1_0aa19aeb",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 444,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-02-25T16:28:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My understanding of skcms is that unpremul should generally be used. I don\u0027t know for sure whether that applies to today\u0027s Skia drawing.\n\nGiven that I\u0027m seeing a regression here, this may be worth exploring.",
      "parentUuid": "61e65f80_ca472483",
      "revId": "9dc6192c17dff2c5f0aae49b51fc2c6c4050d255",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
